						<b>Kongnamul-japchae (bean sprouts with other vegetables)</b><br><br>
						Bean sprouts of which heads and tails are removed are parboiled in salt water and tinged with red pepper powder water. Then they are mixed with carrots, radish, bracken, pear, and pine nuts to give sweet and pungent taste</td>
					</tr>				
